a chamber music player.

00:15:18.530 --> 00:15:21.580
I mean it's just you have
to play louder, of course,

00:15:21.580 --> 00:15:23.360
when you play with orchestra,
but it's still the same thing.

00:15:23.360 --> 00:15:25.070
It's passing from one
voice to another.

00:15:25.070 --> 00:15:30.380
It's conversation, and that goes
all through music, and yeah,

00:15:30.380 --> 00:15:32.790
I also said that some of the
greatest musicians I know,

00:15:32.790 --> 00:15:35.260
in fact a lot of them,
are not soloists.

00:15:35.260 --> 00:15:36.560
They're teachers.

00:15:36.560 --> 00:15:37.860
They're in orchestras.

00:15:37.860 --> 00:15:39.160
They're a chamber music
player, you know,

00:15:39.160 --> 00:15:42.280
as in an established chamber
ensemble, and even listeners,

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:46.490
some listeners I know who
understand so much about music,

00:15:46.490 --> 00:15:49.350
actually even Connie, Connie Shih,
