00:24:20.120 --> 00:24:23.130
First question, I can't think

00:24:23.130 --> 00:24:24.950
of a better expression
than classical music.

00:24:24.950 --> 00:24:28.620
It's very limited, but I think
it's probably less off putting

00:24:28.620 --> 00:24:30.720
than art music.

00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:32.190
I don't know.

00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:35.070
Of course, nowadays the
boundaries are blurred anyway,

00:24:35.070 --> 00:24:41.290
but I mean I'd love it if somebody
came out with a better expression.

00:24:41.290 --> 00:24:42.680
I mean, art music.

00:24:42.680 --> 00:24:44.800
It could-I think that
sounds a bit precious.

00:24:44.800 --> 00:24:47.540
I think classical music is
slightly better than that,

00:24:47.540 --> 00:24:51.990
but it's not perfect, and as
for women composers, well,

00:24:51.990 --> 00:24:56.030
there are now many
wonderful women composers.

00:24:56.030 --> 00:24:58.560
In the past I think
it was a social thing

00:24:58.560 --> 00:25:01.750
that they were discouraged
from studying it.

00:25:01.750 --> 00:25:04.100
They were discouraged from
performing, and through performing,

00:25:04.100 --> 00:25:05.850
of course, you became
more confident.

00:25:05.850 --> 00:25:07.680
You tried things out.

00:25:07.680 --> 00:25:12.010
They were discouraged from playing
with famous people, you know,

00:25:12.010 --> 00:25:13.310
because they couldn't perform.

00:25:13.310 --> 00:25:14.610
They couldn't play
with famous people

00:25:14.610 --> 00:25:15.910 position:56%
who could have influenced them well.

00:25:15.910 --> 00:25:18.830
So I don't-- I can't think
of any great women composers.

00:25:18.830 --> 00:25:20.130
I know some fine ones.

00:25:20.130 --> 00:25:22.120
I think Laura Schumann
wrote beautiful music.

00:25:22.120 --> 00:25:27.710
Fanny Mendelssohn, too, and of
course in the past, Hilda Bingen

00:25:27.710 --> 00:25:31.020
and Chaminade, and there
are a few actually.

00:25:31.020 --> 00:25:34.280
French ones who wrote some
really beautiful music,

00:25:34.280 --> 00:25:39.940
but I think it's changed finally
or it's changing very much now,

00:25:39.940 --> 00:25:41.890
finally, as it is with conductors,

00:25:41.890 --> 00:25:44.670
and now finally we're getting
some really great women conductors

00:25:44.670 --> 00:25:47.910
and composers just
because of social things.

00:25:47.910 --> 00:25:52.060
There were always great women
players, I think, but, again,

00:25:52.060 --> 00:25:54.790
they were-we don't hear so
much about them, you know,

00:25:54.790 --> 00:25:58.270 position:56%
history books because they were
discouraged from performing so much,

00:25:58.270 --> 00:26:01.360
